product_events.product_description: Cellars at Jasper Hill's master cheesemaker, Mateo Kehler, provides his expertise and his cheese cave for 60 quarterly wheels of this special-selected cave-matured 12-month-old clothbound cheddar. Kehler's climate-controlled caves and years of knowledge transform Cabot's cows' milk wheels into a things of beauty, full of sharp caramel notes.

product_events.product_name: Red Leicester with Cracked Black Pepper
product_events.product_description: Shelburne Farms' farmstead cheddar is produced at the former Vanderbilt Estate just outside of Burlington, Vermont, on picturesque Lake Champlain. This cheese is made from the fresh, raw milk of a purebred herd of Brown Swiss cows that roam the meadows around the farm. Aged for over two years, you'll find it sharp, but not peppery, and full of milky goodness, with a delightful lingering fruity finish.

Handcrafted in New York State, this cheese lives up to its triple-X rating with extra-extra-extra sharp flavor. Yancey's Fancy ages this lush white raw-milk cheddar over 18 months to ensure plenty of tangy flavor. Pair up with a bold red wine, a pint of porter or an oatmeal stout.

Pale, creamy, and delicate. A true American original, invented, according to Gold Rush lore, by David Jacks in the 49er boomtown of Monterey, California. Monterey Jack melts beautifully on cheeseburgers, over nachos, and in quesadillas.

category_events.title: Dutch
category_events.description: Dutch cheese production is currently in the hands of dairy factories, which produce and export hundreds of millions of tons of cheese every year. The cheese markets in Alkmaar, Gouda and Edam remind us of the origins of a flourishing cheese trade and have become popular tourist attractions. The Dutch still love cheese and eat about seven pounds of it annually per person. Just like Julius Caesar, let yourself be surprised about the many types of Dutch cheeses and sample the country's "yellow gold".

category_events.title: Fruit & Savoury
category_events.description: Fruit and cheese platters are one of my favorites to make for a party! They are always a show stopper and it’s something I know everyone will love and will get eaten. I tend to stick with “safer” cheeses that I know kids will like too but the sky is the limit with cheese boards. I’ll share lots of variations below.

slogan_events.slogan: HOLEY WEDGE MAKES ME MELT HOLY UNION OF MILK AND PATIENCE WE WAIT, YOU AGE -ANNELIESZ
